                <!-- Introduction -->
                <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 border-l-4 border-brandOrange p-6 rounded-r-xl mb-8">
                    <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">In the world of high-power electronics, a single component failure can lead to a brand-damaging recall. At WOWOHCOOL, our quality control isn't just a final check. It's a rigorous 10-stage engineering process for GaN chargers, power banks, and hybrid 2-in-1 devices.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">This guide reveals exactly how we ensure zero-defect power solutions for B2B buyers. It covers our 10-layer QC system, the Four Pillars of stress testing, and why leading brands trust us with their volume orders.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">According to industry quality standards (<a href="https://www.iso.org/standard/54066.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">ISO 2859/AQL</a>), the acceptable defect rate for consumer electronics is 0.65-1.0%, with premium OEM manufacturers maintaining rates below 0.5% through rigorous testing protocols.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">According to the <a href="https://www.cpsc.gov/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">US Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC)</a>, overheating and fire risks accounted for 65% of electronic charger-related recall incidents between 2020-2025, underlining the critical importance of stringent QC processes.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">In June 2026, a <a href="https://www.which.co.uk/news/article/dangerous-phone-chargers-for-sale-on-online-marketplaces-aMLru0N1234X" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange underline">Which? investigation</a> exposed "potentially lethal" counterfeit chargers sold on Amazon Haul, B&Q, and eBay, some filled with modeling clay instead of proper circuits. These chargers failed basic hi-pot and insulation resistance tests, posing electrocution and fire risks to consumers.</p>

                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-0">At <a href="/about" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">WOWOHCOOL</a>, we've maintained a defect rate under 0.3% since 2013. Our <a href="/service/" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">ISO 9001:2015 certified facility</a> handles over 5 million units annually for global brands.</p>
                </div>
